```json
{
"application": "SLaPMapper",
"other_software": [
"bowtie2",
"trimmomatic"
],
"resource_requirements": {
"cpu": "10",
"memory": "20GB",
"scratch_local": "30GB",
"walltime": "02:00:00"
}
}
```

The script utilizes SLaPMapper, a software tool for RNA-seq mapping. It leverages other tools like bowtie2 for alignment and trimmomatic for read preprocessing.  

The script is configured to run on a cluster using the PBS (Portable Batch System) scheduler. It requests 10 CPUs, 20GB of memory, 30GB of local scratch space, and a maximum walltime of 2 hours. 

It also makes use of modulefiles for loading the necessary software packages on the cluster.
